      "content": "A buffer of at least 45 minutes between the Heathrow Express arrival and your LNER departure from King's Cross is advisable. This gives you ample time to navigate the stations, which can be a bit hectic, and absorb any minor delays. It's always safer to have wiggle room when making connections, especially when traveling between major hubs. I'd recommend checking the live departure boards when you arrive at King's Cross before sprinting to your platform! If you're feeling nervous, book a taxi from King's Cross to the LNER departure area just as a backup plan.",
      "source": "target",
