      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "King's Cross is indeed vast, and the main bottleneck can be navigating the crowds, not just the walk itself. Look out for the main concourse area where different lines converge; it can feel like a maze during peak travel times. Also, be mindful of the escalator and lift queues, which can build up quickly, even if the track changes aren't the issue. Trying to move with the general flow of travelers is often the fastest way through the chaos.",
      "source": "target",
